on_detail%3Fid%3D1668624.015%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EOSHA%20records%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Amazon%2C%20which%20earns%20hundreds%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famazon-earnings%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ebillions%20in%20revenue%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20each%20quarter%2C%20was%20slapped%20with%20a%20%247%2C000%20fine%2C%20the%20maximum%20penalty%20in%20the%20state%2C%20even%20though%20Indiana%20regulators%20found%20that%20the%20warehouse%20could%20have%20done%20more%20to%20fix%20or%20manage%20hazards%20that%20were%20%26quot%3Bcausing%20or%20likely%20to%20cause%20death%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20Post%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere's%20no%20real%20financial%20incentive%20for%20an%20employer%20like%20Amazon%20to%20change%20their%20working%20environment%20to%20make%20it%20more%20safe%2C%26quot%3B%20Stephen%20Wagner%2C%20an%20attorney%20based%20in%20Indiana%2C%20told%20the%20Post.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20study%20in%20April%20that%20used%20OSHA's%20data%20found%20that%20the%20rate%20of%20worker%20injuries%20at%20Amazon%20was%2070%25%20higher%20than%20those%20at%20similar%20warehouses%2C%20and%20the%20rate%20of%20serious%20injuries%20was%20double%20that%20of%20other%20warehouses.%20OSHA%20has%20previously%20found%20that%20several%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finvestigation-sdny-amazon-hid-injuries-defraud-lenders-2023-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EAmazon%20warehouses%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20failed%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.osha.gov%2Fnews%2Fnewsreleases%2Fnational%2F12162022%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ereport%20worker%20injuries%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20past.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERegulators%20have%20also%20criticized%20Amazon's%20focus%20on%20speed%20at%20its%20warehouses%2C%20which%20resulted%20in%20workers%20%26quot%3Bawkwardly%20twisting%2C%20bending%20and%20extending%20themselves%20to%20lift%20items%2C%26quot%3B