%94%20the%20implosion%20of%20an%20entire%20nation%2C%20the%20scale%20of%20its%20refugee%20crisis%20and%20the%20West%E2%80%99s%20indifference.%20%E2%80%A6%20I%20wanted%20to%20deepen%20the%20reader%E2%80%99s%20immersion%20to%20such%20a%20degree%20that%20by%20the%20end%20of%20the%20book%2C%20they%20would%20not%20just%20know%2C%20but%20feel%20this%20problem%20for%20themselves.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDecision%20influenced%20by%20%E2%80%98timeless%E2%80%99%20theme%20of%20book%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECanadian%20writer%20Esi%20Edugyan%2C%20who%20chaired%20the%20judging%20panel%2C%20said%20the%20book%20is%20%E2%80%9Ca%20triumph%20of%20emotional%20storytelling%2C%20bracing%20and%20brave%E2%80%9D%20in%20which%20Lynch%20%E2%80%9Cpulls%20off%20feats%20of%20language%20that%20are%20stunning%20to%20witness.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELynch%E2%80%99s%20win%20comes%20days%20after%20far-right%20violence%20erupted%20in%20Ireland%E2%80%99s%20capital%2C%20Dublin%2C%20following%20a%20stabbing%20attack%20outside%20a%20primary%20school.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEdugyan%20said%20recent%20events%20had%20come%20up%20during%20their%20discussions%20to%20choose%20a%20winner%2C%20but%20it%20was%20not%20the%20reason%20the%20book%20won.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELynch%E2%80%99s%20book%20%E2%80%9Ccaptures%20the%20social%20and%20political%20anxieties%20of%20our%20current%20moment%E2%80%9D%20but%20also%20deals%20with%20%E2%80%9Ctimeless%E2%80%9D%20themes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEdugyan%20said%20the%20choice%20of%20winner%20wasn%E2%80%99t%20unanimous%2C%20but%20the%20meeting%2C%20which%20lasted%20six%20hours%2C%20was%20%E2%80%9Ccollegial.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELynch%20received%20his%20trophy%20from%20last%20year%E2%80%99s%20winner%2C%20Sri%20Lankan%20author%20Shehan%20Karunatilaka%2C%20who%20won%20for%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Seven%20Moons%20of%20Maali%20Almeida%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20a%20novel%20about%20the%20trauma%20of%20the%20civil%20war%20in%20his%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20report%20first%20appeared%20on%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Firish-author-paul-lynch-wins-booker-prize-for-prophet-song%2Fa-67558992%5C%22%3EDW%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1701056422000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F27090716%2FUntitled-design-6-2.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Firish-writer-paul-lynch-wins-booker-prize-for-prophet-song%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Lynch's%20novel%20depicts%20an%20Ireland%20descending%20into%20totalitarianism%20in%20the%20near%20future.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A8%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Firish-writer-paul-lynch-wins-booker-prize-for-prophet-song%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22When%20the%20Ceasefire%20Ends%2C%20Biden%20Shouldn't%20Allow%20Israel%20to%20Continue%20Its%20Futile%20War%20of%20Reprisal%20in%20Gaza%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F27090342%2Fimage1170x530cropped-6.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20war%20in%20Gaza%20reaching%20the%2050-day%20mark%2C%20239%20hostages%20are%20still%20being%20held%20by%20Hamas%20and%20the%20Islamic%20Jihad%2C%20Israeli%20soldiers%20are%20inside%20Gaza%20City%2C%20and%20as%20a%20result%20of%20Israel%E2%80%99s%20bombing%20campaign%20countless%20buildings%20have%20been%20destroyed%20in%20the%20Northen%20part%20of%20the%20Strip%20and%20an%20unbearable%20number%20of%20civilians%20including%20children%20have%20been%20killed.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAs%20the%20ICC%20chief%20prosecutor%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.icc-cpi.int%2Fnews%2Fstatement-icc-prosecutor-karim-khan-kc-cairo-situation-state-palestine-and-israel%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Estated%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20during%20his%20visit%20to%20Cairo%2C%20Israel%20needs%20to%20demonstrate%20that%20any%20attack%20that%20impacted%20innocent%20civilians%20or%20protected%20objects%20was%20conducted%20in%20accordance%20with%20the%20international%20law%20and%20specifically%20the%20principles%20of%20distinction%2C%20precaution%20and%20of%20proportionality.%20Even%20if%20Israel%20succeeds%20in%20doing%20this%2C%3C%2Fspan%3E%20%3Cspan%3Esomething%20that%20seems%20very%20challenging%20in%20view%20of%20the%20extent%20of%20the%20destruction%20it%20caused%20in%20Gaza%2C%20the%20question%20arises%3A%20what%20is%20the%20endgame%3F%3C%2Fspan%3E%20%3Cspan%3ETo%20really%20overthrow%20the%20Hamas%20regime%2C%20as%20the%20Biden%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.haaretz.co.il%2Fnews%2Fpolitics%2F2023-11-04%2Fty-article%2F.premium%2F0000018b-993e-db71-a7df-fdffa3220000%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eadministration%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20and%20Netanyahu%E2%80%99s%20government%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ynet.co.il%2Fnews%2Farticle%2Fryx6v11sm6%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Edeclared%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20or%20just%20take%20reprisal%20on%20Hamas%20for%20the%20atrocities%20and%20crimes%20it%20committed%20since%20October%207.%20This%20question%20is%20particularly%20important%20now%20since%20there%20is%20a%20question%20of%20what%20will%20happen%20after%20the%20short%20cease%20fire%20ends.%20The%20war%20may%20drag%20on%20for%20a%20long%20time%20while%20the%20number%20of%20Palestinian%20and%20Israeli%20civilians%20who%20will%20be%20harmed%20will%20only%20increase.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20is%20clear%20that%20the%20only%20suitable%20replacement%20to%20the%20Hamas%20regime%20in%20Gaza%20is%20the%20Palestinian%20Authority%20(PA).%20Theoretically%2C%20this%20should%20not%20be%20complicated%2C%20since%20although%20Hamas%20in%20its%20military%20coup%20in%202007%20murdered%20some%20of%20the%20PA%E2%80%99s%20officials%2C%20it%20kept%20a%20large%20part%20of%20its%20bureaucrats%20in%20their%20positions.%20But%2C%20politically%20and%20rightfully%2C%20the%20PA%20will%20not%20be%20able%20to%20agree%20to%20such%20a%20thing%20while%20Israel%20continues%20its%20accelerated%20ethnic%20cleansing%20and%20apartheid%20in%20the%20West%20Bank.%3C%2Fspan%3E%20%3Cspan%3EIn%20their%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.haaretz.co.il%2Fnews%2Fpolitics%2F2023-11-05%2Fty-article%2F.premium%2F0000018b-9f50-dbad-abfb-dfdc253f0000%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Emeeting%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20on%20November%205%2C%20Palestinian%20President%20Mahmoud%20Abbas%20told%20the%20US%20Secretary%20of%20State%20Antony%20Blinken%20that%20the%20PA%20is%20ready%20to%20accept%20full%20responsibility%20for%20the%20Gaza%20Strip%20only%20as%20part%20of%20a%20comprehensive%20political%20solution.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20is%20why%20Prime%20Minister%20Benjamin%20Netanyahu%20seems%20to%20be%20bluffing.%20In%20order%20to%20topple%20the%20Hamas%20regime%2C%20he%20will%20have%20to%20topple%20his%20own%20regime.%20Netanyahu%20only%20cares%20about%20his%20own%20political%20survival%20and%20for%20achieving%20that%20goal%20he%20is%20completely%20dependent%20on%20his%20coalition%20with%20the%20far-right%20parties%20which%20sees%20the%20Palestinian%20Authority%20and%20any%20political%20agreement%20with%20it%20as%20a%20bigger%20threat%20than%20Hamas.%20For%20example%2C%20on%20August%2031%2C%202021%2C%20the%20far-right%20and%20supporter%20of%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.middleeasteye.net%2Fopinion%2Fisrael-us-bezalel-smotrich-evidence-genocide-support%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Egenocide%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20Minister%20Bezalel%20Smotritz%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fkol-barama.co.il%2Fitem%2F%2525D7%252594%2525D7%252590%2525D7%252596%2525D7%252599%2525D7%2525A0%2525D7%252595-%2525D7%252594%2525D7%252590%2525D7%25259D-%2525D7%2525A1%2525D7%25259E%2525D7%252595%2525D7%252598%2525D7%2525A8%2525D7%252599%2525D7%2525A5-%2525D7%25259E%2525D7%252590%2525D7%2525A9%2525D7%252599%2525D7%25259D-%2525D7%252590%2525D7%2525AA-%2525D7%252591%2525D7%2525A0%2525D7%252598-%2525D7%252591%2525D7%25259E%2525D7%252595%2525D7%2525AA%2525D7%252595%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eexplained%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20in%20an%20interview%20(as%20an%20Member%20of%20Knesset)%20%E2%80%9CIn%20some%20respects%2C%20the%20Palestinian%20Authority%20is%20more%20dangerous%20to%20Israel%20than%20Hamas.%20The%20Palestinian%20Authority%20is%20a%20strategic%20threat.%20On%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20Hamas%20is%20a%20tactical%20threat%20that%20can%20be%20managed.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%20%3Cspan%3EThis%20month%2C%20on%20November%203%2C%20Minister%20Smotritz%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.inn.co.il%2Fnews%2F618914%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Esaid%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20Palestinian%20Authority%20is%20not%20the%20solution%20%E2%80%93%20it%20is%20part%20of%20the%20problem.%20We%20do%20not%20repeat%20mistakes%20and%20concepts%20that%20blew%20up%20in%20our%20faces.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAlthough%20Netanyahu%20could%20have%20formed%20an%20alternative%20emergency%20coalition%2C%20even%20temporarily%2C%20only%20the%20far-right%20parties%20are%20willing%20to%20abolish%20the%20independence%20of%20the%20judiciary%20that%20Netanyahu%20needs%20in%20order%20to%20cancel%20or%20stop%20his%20criminal%20trial%20or%20render%20it%20meaningless.%20The%20far-right%20parties%20will%20also%20help%20Netanyahu%20establish%20a%20toothless%20commission%20of%20inquiry%20into%20responsibility%20for%20the%20October%207%20disaster.%3C%2Fspan%3E%20%3Cspan%3EWe%20recently%20saw%20an%20example%20of%20Netanyahu%E2%80%99s%20deep%20attachment%20to%20the%20far-right%20when%20he%20chose%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.haaretz.com%2Fisrael-news%2F2023-11-05%2Fty-article%2Fnetanyahu-criticizes-minister-who-suggested-option-of-dropping-nuclear-bomb-on-gaza%2F0000018b-9e7b-db71-a7df-ffffe4510000%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Enot%20to%20fire%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20the%20far-right%20Minister%20Amichai%20Eliyahu%20despite%20the%20huge%20international%20damage%20he%20caused%20to%20Israel%20when%20he%20said%20that%20dropping%20a%20nuclear%20weapon%20on%20the%20Gaza%20Strip%20is%20%E2%80%9Can%20option.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20is%20not%20difficult%20to%20imagine%20that%20in%20a%20few%20weeks%20from%20now%2C%20after%20many%20more%20Gazan%20civilians%20will%20be%20killed%20and%20most%20of%20the%20hostages%20from%20Israel%20will%20still%20not%20be%20released%2C%20Netanyahu%20will%20have%20a%20celebratory%20press%20conference%20where%20he%20will%20announce%20that%20Israel%20has%20exacted%20a%20heavy%20price%20on%20Hamas%2C%20killed%20thousands%20of%20terrorists%20and%20destroyed%20its%20military%20infrastructure%2C%20but%20in%20practice%20will%20allow%20Hamas%20rule%20to%20continue.%20In%20order%20to%20satisfy%20many%20in%20the%20Israeli%20public%20who%20trusted%20the%20declarations%20of%20his%20government%2C%20Netanyahu%20will%20probably%20claim%20that%20he%20wanted%20to%20overthrow%20the%20Hamas%20regime%20but%20the%20international%20community%20stopped%20him.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20US%20has%20known%20for%20long%20that%20Israel%20has%20a%20strategy%20of%20reprisal.%20According%20to%20a%20US%20Defense%20Intelligence%20Agency%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cia.gov%2Freadingroom%2Fdocs%2FCIA-RDP92T00277R000600150004-1.pdf%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eappraisal%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20with%20the%20title%20%E2%80%9CIsrael%3A%20experience%20in%20combating%20terror%E2%80%9D%2C%20that%20was%20made%20on%20June%2011%2C%201984%2C%20and%20declassified%20in%202016%2C%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20commitment%20to%20a%20reprisal%20policy%20is%20deeply%20ingrained%20in%20the%20Israeli%20military%20establishment.%20Although%20Israeli%20military%20intelligence%20officials%20have%20consistently%20warned%20that%20such%20actions%20have%20had%20little%20deterrent%20effect%20on%20terrorists%2C%20the%20leadership%20has%20shown%20a%20willingness%20to%20take%20action%20if%20Israel%E2%80%99s%20security%20interests%20are%20at%20stake%E2%80%9D.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20document%20explains%20how%20from%20the%201950s%20until%20the%201980s%2C%20Israel%20%E2%80%9Cmoved%20from%20a%20policy%20of%20simple%20eye%20for%20an%20eye%20operation%20to%20a%20fully%20developed%20doctrine%20of%20retaliation.%20This%20held%20that%20terrorism%20could%20be%20countered%20by%20placing%20an%20unacceptably%20high%20price%20(to%20the%20Arabs)%20on%20such%20operations%E2%80%9D.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAlso%20mentioned%20are%20the%20difficulties%20that%20Israel%20faces%20today%20in%20Gaza%2C%20%E2%80%9CNo%20matter%20how%20expertly%20conducted%20from%20a%20military%20perspective%2C%20IDF%20operations%20against%20terrorists%20operating%20from%20bases%20in%20civilian%20areas%20damaged%20Israel%E2%80%99s%20prestige%2C%20the%20image%20of%20its%20military%2C%20and%20its%20relations%20with%20friendly%20states.%20Another%20cost%20%E2%80%9Cis%20the%20extent%20to%20which%20Israel%E2%80%99s%20confrontational%20approach%20for%20dealing%20with%20terrorism%20contributed%20to%20its%20perpetuation.%20Israel%E2%80%99s%20large-scale%20actions%20satisfied%20the%20Palestinian%20goal%20of%20eliciting%20a%20strong%20Israeli%20response%2C%20bringing%20attention%2C%20and%20sometimes%20sympathy%2C%20to%20the%20terrorist%20cause.%20Furthermore%2C%20the%20Israeli%20approach%20does%20not%20appear%20to%20have%20hampered%20recruitment%20of%20Palestinians%20willing%20to%20die%20for%20their%20cause.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAs%20the%20US%20Defense%20Intelligence%20Agency%20appraisal%20concludes%2C%20%E2%80%9Capproach%20to%20terrorism%20that%20relies%20primarily%20on%20force%20creates%20a%20dynamic%20of%20stimulus%20and%20response%2C%20rather%20than%20a%20clear%20end%20to%20the%20problem%E2%80%9D.%20The%20only%20solution%20to%20the%20problem%20of%20the%20Gaza%20Strip%2C%20as%20well%20as%20to%20the%20entire%20Israeli-Palestinian%20conflict%2C%20is%20diplomatic%20and%20not%20military.%3C%2Fspan%3E%20%3Cspan%3EPresident%20Biden%20should%20not%20allow%20Israel%20to%20continue%20to%20wage%20a%20war%20of%20futile%20reprisal%2C%20which%20will%20solve%20nothing%20and%20only%20cause%20more%20human%20suffering.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EEitay%20Mack%20is%20an%20Israeli%20human%20rights%20lawyer%20and%20activist.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1701056102000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F27090342%2Fimage1170x530cropped-6.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fgaza-biden-ceasefire-pause%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20only%20solution%20to%20the%20problem%20of%20the%20Gaza%20Strip%2C%20as%20well%20as%20to%20the%20entire%20Israeli-Palestinian%20conflict%2C%20is%20diplomatic%20and%20not%20military.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A7%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fgaza-biden-ceasefire-pause%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Stock%20market%20holiday%3A%20BSE%2C%20NSE%20closed%20today%20due%20to%20Guru%20Nanak%20Jayanti%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1701055924000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fbsmedia.business-standard.com%2F_media%2Fbs%2Fimg%2Farticle%2F2023-09%2F25%2Ffull%2F1695612851-2693.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fmarkets%2Fnews%2Fstock-market-holidays-nse-bse-closed-on-november-27-for-guru-nanak-jayanti-123112700101_1.html%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Stock%20market%20holiday%20today%3A%20Including%20November%2027%2C%20the%20Indian%20stock%20market%20has%20remained%20closed%20for%2013%20weekdays%