%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22West%20Bank%3A%20Eight%20Palestinians%20killed%20during%20Israeli%20raid%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1701008168000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fichef.bbci.co.uk%2Fnews%2F1024%2Fbranded_news%2F6470%2Fproduction%2F_131821752_gettyimages-1802888517-594x594.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-middle-east-67535965%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20Israeli%20army%20says%20it%20was%20mounting%20a%20raid%20in%20the%20city%20of%20Jenin%20to%20capture%20a%20Palestinian%20suspect.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A61%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-middle-east-67535965%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-bbc-co-uk.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-middle-east-67535965.amp%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-middle-east-67535965.amp%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Men%2C%20Women%20and%20the%20Gendered%20Life%20of%20Labour%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F26193441%2F25420931940_7fa4ebfe87_c.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cstrong%3ESaakhi%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20is%20a%20Sunday%20column%20from%20Mrinal%20Pande%2C%20in%20which%20she%20writes%20about%20what%20she%20sees%20and%20also%20participates%20in.%20That%20has%20been%20her%20burden%20to%20bear%20ever%20since%20she%20embarked%20on%20a%20life%20as%20a%20journalist%2C%20writer%2C%20editor%2C%20author%2C%20and%20chairperson%20of%20Prasar%20Bharti.%20Her%20journey%20of%20being%20a%20witness-participant%20continues.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EEver%20since%20Dr%20Narayana%20Murthy%2C%20founder%20of%20the%20tech%20giant%20Infosys%2C%20spoke%20of%20the%20need%20for%20young%20Indians%20to%20work%20longer%20(at%20least%2070%20hours%20a%20week)%2C%20his%20words%20have%20triggered%20a%20big%20debate%20on%20work%20patterns%20within%20India.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EPublic%20figures%20have%20often%20said%20Indian%20workers%20are%20somewhat%20indisciplined%20and%20shirk%20work%20unless%20driven%20by%20an%20iron%20hand.%20They%20are%20pleased%20by%20Dr%20Murthy%E2%80%99s%20words%20that%20working%20longer%20hours%20was%20how%20Europe%20had%20recreated%20its%20lost%20wealth%20after%20the%20World%20Wars.%20So%20if%20India%20is%20to%20compete%20with%20global%20manufacturing%20hubs%20like%20China%2C%20its%20young%20workers%20must%20work%20harder%20and%20for%20longer%20hours.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20317px)%2085vw%2C%20317px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F03%2F05103945%2FIMG_1783.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Mrinal%20Pande%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22317%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F03%2F05103945%2FIMG_1783.jpg%20525w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F03%2F05103945%2FIMG_1783-246x300.jpg%20246w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-642789%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22386%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EIllustration%3A%20Pariplab%20Chakraborty%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESuch%20an%20easy%20linking%20of%20long%20work%20hours%20with%20bigger%20and%20better%20outputs%2C%20is%20essentially%20a%20part%20of%20thinking%20that%20peaks%20in%20a%20technocratic%20contempt%20for%20philosophical%20talk%20about%20liberty%2C%20equality%20and%20fraternity.%20When%20one%20of%20the%20retired%20kings%20of%20the%20hi-tech%20corporate%20world%20speaks%2C%20India%20listens.%20Among%20many%2C%20it%20strengthens%20the%20belief%20that%20most%20workers%20are%20a%20herd%20%E2%80%93%20often%20ridiculed%20%E2%80%93%20away%20from%20the%20mic%20of%20course%2C%20for%20their%20lack%20of%20scientific%20acumen%2C%20and%20so%20they%20must%20be%20nudged%20with%20suitable%20labour%20laws%20apart%20from%20being%20directed%20and%20kept%20under%20surveillance%20for%20data%20collection.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBy%20harvesting%20such%20raw%20data%2C%20a%20further%20tweaking%20of%20more%20manipulatory%20laws%20to%20make%20production%20of%20goods%20cheaper%20than%20China%E2%80%99s%20can%20become%20a%20reality.%20The%20basic%2C%20perhaps%20unconscious%2C%20assumption%20behind%20this%20has%20some%20backing%20of%20the%20caste%20system%20as%20well%3A%20ordinary%20workers%20are%20to%20be%20ruled%20and%20tolerated%20only%20up%20to%20a%20point.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20is%20time%20we%20examined%20caste%2C%20class%20and%20gender%20privileges%20in%20a%20social%20context%2C%20as%20embedded%20in%20the%20Indian%20industry%20and%20political%20space%2C%20through%20the%20eyes%20of%20those%20it%20has%20routinely%20overlooked.%20Chances%20are%20a%20legalised%20work%20ethic%20that%20will%20promote%20longer%20working%20hours%20in%20the%20name%20of%20nation%20building%20via%20industrial%20production%2C%20will%20again%20measure%20work%20hours%20as%20%E2%80%98man%20hours%E2%80%99.%20This%20verbal%20term%20genderises%20work%20by%20attaching%20a%20greater%20value%20to%20work%20being%20done%20by%20males.%20With%20that%2C%20female%20workers%20in%20factories%2C%20fields%20and%20other%20types%20of%20industrial%20jobs%20turn%20into%20invisible%20entities%2C%20always%20to%20be%20spoken%20for%20and%20never%20consulted%20about%20their%20work%20experience%20as%20women%2C%20when%20in%20fact%2C%20their%20productive%20and%20reproductive%20roles%20are%20simultaneous.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20original%20Factories%E2%80%99%20Act%20of%201948%2C%20which%20is%20being%20increasingly%20challenged%2C%20had%20stipulated%20that%20an%20adult%20worker%20cannot%20work%20for%20more%20than%2048%20hours%20per%20week%2C%20and%20nine%20hours%20if%20paid%20extra.%20The%20Act%20also%20prohibits%20women%20working%20between%207-8%20pm%20and%209%3A30-10%20pm%2C%20thus%20freeing%20the%20employers%20of%20the%20burden%20of%20organising%20transport%20facilities%20but%20limiting%20women%E2%80%99s%20access%20to%20jobs%20that%20need%20workers%20to%20perform%20during%20those%20hours.%20Workers%2C%20the%20Act%20says%2C%20must%20not%20work%20more%20than%2010%20and%20a%20half%20hours.%20And%20that%20includes%20a%20lunch%20break.%20The%20states%20of%20Karnataka%20and%20Tamil%20Nadu%20have%20already%20amended%20the%20Act%20and%20extended%20work%20hours%20to%2012%20hours%20for%20factory%20workers%20who%2C%20in%20fact%2C%20work%20even%20longer%20hours.%20The%20ILO%20data%20for%202023%20says%20we%20already%20rank%20number%20seven%20among%20nations%2C%20where%20workers%20work%2047.7%20hours%20per%20week.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EGiven%20the%20overall%20educational%20and%20health%20patterns%20of%20our%20ordinary%20workers%20and%20poor%20quality%20of%20infrastructure%20and%20tools%2C%20an%20average%20Indian%20worker%E2%80%99s%20performance%20peters%20out%20after%20seven%20years%2C%20according%20to%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thelancet.com%2Fjournals%2Flancet%2Farticle%2FPIIS0140-6736(18)31941-X%2Ffulltext%5C%22%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3ELancet%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20In%20the%20global%20list%20of%20long%20peak%20productive%20years%20among%20workers%2C%20India%20stands%20at%20158%20among%20195%20nations.%20Be%20it%20noted%20here%20that%20by%202027%2C%20it%20will%20have%20the%20largest%20workforce%20globally%20(18.6%25%20of%20total).%20Given%20the%20present%20levels%20of%20education%2C%20health%20and%20social%20care%2C%20and%20quality%20of%20tools%20and%20infrastructures%20they%20handle%2C%20a%20higher%20productivity%20only%20through%20subjecting%20them%20to%20longer%20work%20hours%2C%20is%20rather%20unlikely.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20point%20raised%20by%20Murthy%20merits%20attention%2C%20but%20the%20first%20question%20we%20should%20actually%20ask%20is%20what%20do%20Indian%20workers%2C%20especially%20women%2C%20need%20beyond%20a%20%E2%80%98safe%20space%E2%80%99%20and%20a%20revised%20salary%20to%20achieve%20peak%20performance%20levels%3F%20How%20helpful%2C%20how%20unbiased%20will%20the%20socio-legal%20perceptions%20be%20towards%20helping%20our%20invisibilised%20working%20women%20if%20the%20labour%20laws%20are%20revised%20%3F%20A%20major%20English%20daily%20recently%20quoted%20a%20judgment%20from%20the%20Madras%20high%20court%20delivered%20on%20June%2023%2C%20that%20sums%20up%20the%20current%20perceptions%20on%20gender%3A%20%E2%80%9C%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fcity%2Fchennai%2Fhc-homemakers-entitled-to-equal-share-in-property%2Farticleshow%2F101250062.cms%23%3A~%3Atext%3D%25E2%2580%259CIn%2520generality%2520of%2520marriages%252C%2520the%2C%252C%25E2%2580%259D%2520Justice%2520Krishnan%2520Ramasamy%2520said.%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20generality%20of%20marriages%2C%20the%20wife%20bears%20and%20rears%20children%20and%20minds%20the%20home.%20She%20thereby%20frees%20her%20husband%20for%20his%20economic%20activities.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20is%20the%20ground%20reality%20women%20see%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Eaankhon%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%20%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Eki%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%20%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Edekhi%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20as%20Kabir%20says.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%98Does%20your%20man%20or%20family%20approve%3F%E2%80%99%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%98How%20do%20your%20children%20cope%20after%20school%20hours%3F%E2%80%99%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThese%20are%20questions%20never%20posed%20to%20male%20employees.%20Unsurprisingly%2C%20according%20to%20the%20NSSO%2C%20on%20an%20average%2C%20male%20salaried%20employees%20earn%201.2-1.3%20times%20more%20than%20their%20female%20colleagues.%20And%20while%20men%20spend%20150%20minutes%20more%20per%20day%20as%20paid%20employees%2C%20working%20women%20spend%20twice%20the%20time%20than%20males%20in%20carrying%20out%20domestic%20duties%20within%20homes%20and%20have%2024%25%20less%20leisure%20time%20than%20the%20males.%20Time%20poverty%20eats%20up%20a%20woman%E2%80%99s%20energies%20and%20work%20potential%20all%20through%20her%20working%20life.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F02%2F14083452%2FUntitled-design-11.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F02%2F14083452%2FUntitled-design-11.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F02%2F14083452%2FUntitled-design-11-300x169.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F02%2F14083452%2FUntitled-design-11-1024x576.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-640375%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22675%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ERepresentative%20image%20of%20a%20labourer%20at%20work%20in%20Rajasthan.%20Photo%3A%20Eric%20Parker%2FFlickr%20(CC%20BY-NC%202.0)%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBeing%20pro-women%20is%20now%20the%20politically%20correct%20stance%20even%20for%20the%20most%20extreme%20right-wing%20parties.%20But%20governments%20that%20launch%20a%20thousand%20schemes%20to%20save%2C%20educate%20the%20girl%20child%20and%20make%20women%E2%80%99s%20domestic%20lives%20better%20barely%20think%20of%20raising%20salaries%20and%20social%20safety%20levels%20for%20improving%20lives%20of%20rural%20women%20workers%20like%20those%20under%20the%20ASHA%20or%20landless%20farm%20labourers.%20Neither%20they%20nor%20the%20corporate%20honchos%20who%20mobilise%20Corporate%20Social%20Responsibility%20budgets%20for%20empowering%20women%20actually%20see%20the%20irony%20of%20the%20obvious%20clash%20between%20better%20lives%20for%20workers%20with%20poor%20health%20and%20educational%20backgrounds%20being%20burdened%20with%20longer%20hours%20so%20India%20can%20compete%20better%20with%20China!%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOne%20fears%20the%20impact%20of%20longer%20work%20hours%20will%20be%20to%20create%20job%20pressures%20that%20will%20automatically%20squeeze%20women%20out%20of%20the%20formal%20work%20force.%20The%20alarming%20attrition%20of%20numbers%20of%20women%20employed%20in%20India%E2%80%99s%20formal%20sector%20in%20the%20last%20decade%20is%20already%20indicating%20this.%20And%20the%20glossy%20magazines%20celebrating%2020%20or%20200%20%E2%80%98power%20women%E2%80%99%20in%20their%20annual%20conclaves%20are%20still%20not%20asking%20women%20who%20have%20arrived%20about%20their%20feelings%20of%20conflict%2C%20about%20their%20specific%20needs%20neglected%2C%20about%20the%20terminal%20guilt%20for%20leaving%20home%20each%20day%20and%20getting%20back%20late%2C%20being%20constantly%20deepened%20by%20jibes%20at%20work%20place%20and%20in%20the%20social%20media%2C%20about%20the%20assumptions%20that%20only%20%E2%80%98poor%20women%20work%20because%20they%20have%20to%E2%80%99.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMost%20of%20the%20labour%20in%20the%20world%20is%20done%20by%20women%20and%20that%20is%20a%20fact.%20If%20the%20right%20to%20education%20for%20the%20girl%20child%20is%20a%20stepping%20stone%2C%20towards%20freedom%2C%20it%20has%20to%20have%20the%20road%20ahead%20paved%20with%20other%20kinds%20of%20stepping%20stones%20and%20action.%20To%20be%20sure%2C%20growing%20at%20a%20fast%20pace%20is%20a%20positive%20goal.%20But%20it%20is%20equally%20important%20to%20remain%20in%20the%20present%2C%20remain%20open%2C%20spontaneous%20and%20flexible.%20Because%20our%20gender-polarised%20corporate%20and%20political%20worlds%20simultaneously%20need%20to%20face%20the%20challenges%20posed%20by%20global%20climate%20changes.%20The%20extreme%20heat%20and%20humidity%20waiting%20around%20the%20corner%20and%20the%20pollution%20caused%20by%20carbon%20emissions%20and%20rising%20temperatures%2C%20are%20already%20affecting%20workers%E2%80%99%20productivity%20and%20increasing%20absenteeism%20in%20industry.%20According%20to%20a%20national%20panel%20of%20Indian%20factories%E2%80%99%20report%2C%20annual%20plant%20output%20will%20fall%20by%202%25%20per%20degree%20rise%20in%20temperature.%20This%20year%E2%80%99s%20Rabi%20crop%20sowing%20is%20also%20down%20by%20several%20lakh%20hectares%20as%20water%20tables%20dry%20up.%20By%202030%20heat%20stress%20may%20cause%20a%20loss%20of%203.4%20crore%20jobs%20and%20even%20the%20RBI%20admits%20if%20that%20happens%20it%20will%20deeply%20impact%20the%20GDP.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAn%20obsession%20with%20fast-paced%20development%20that%20measures%20progress%20only%20in%20terms%20of%20corporate%20outputs%20to%20challenge%20China%2C%20we%20can%20already%20see%20it%20erode%20agrarian%20land%20and%20jobs%2C%20raze%20water%20sources%20and%20literally%20bring%20down%20the%20Himalayas%2C%20our%20protector%20for%20centuries.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fauthor%2Fmrinal-pande%5C%22%3EMrinal%20Pande%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20a%20writer%20and%20veteran%20journalist.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1701007606000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F26193441%2F25420931940_7fa4ebfe87_c.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flabour%2Fmen-women-and-the-gendered-life-of-labour%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22When%20one%20of%20the%20retired%20kings%20of%20the%20hi-tech%20corporate%20world%20speaks%20on%20work%20hours%2C%20India%20listens.%20Yet%2C%20much%20remains%20unsaid.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A8%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flabour%2Fmen-women-and-the-gendered-life-of-labour%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22For%20some%20Israeli%20hostage%20families%2C%20the%20painful%20wait%20goes%20on%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1701004135000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fichef.bbci.co.uk%2Fnews%2F1024%2Fbranded_news%2F4026%2Fproduction%2F_131822461_dsc06380.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-middle-east-67536423%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22There%20was%20a%20mix%20of%20hope%20and%20fear%20this%20weekend%20for%20the%20families%20of%20hostages%20expected%20to%20remain%20in%20Gaza.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A61%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-middle-east-67536423%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-bbc-co-uk.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-middle-east-67536423.amp%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-middle-east-67536423.amp%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22It's%20More%20Than%20Just%20TikTok%3A%20How%20the%20Talk%20on%20Palestine%20Shifted%20from%20Territory%20to%20Rights%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F26180940%2FUNI448902_0.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EMuch%20has%20been%20written%20in%20recent%20weeks%20about%20the%20growing%20%E2%80%9Cgenerational%20divide%E2%80%9D%20in%20American%20public%20opinion%20on%20Israel%20and%20Palestine%2C%20and%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.washingtonpost.com%2Ftechnology%2F2023%2F10%2F10%2Ftiktok-hamas-israel-war-videos%2F%5C%22%3Ea%20majority%20of%20the%20writing%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0has%20chosen%20to%20focus%20on%20the%20means%20by%20which%20young%20people%20receive%20information.%20The%20video%20sharing%20app%20TikTok%20has%2C%20understandably%2C%20been%20at%20the%20centre%20of%20these%20discussions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20per%20the%20Reuters%20Institute%20for%20the%20Study%20of%20Journalism%E2%80%99s%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Fbusiness%2Fmedia-telecom%2Ffewer-people-trust-traditional-media-more-turn-tiktok-news-report-says-2023-06-13%2F%5C%22%3Eannual%20report%20released%20in%20June%202023%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%2020%25%20of%2018-24%20year%20olds%20in%20the%20US%20use%20TikTok%20for%20news.%20This%20is%20also%20the%20demographic%20in%20the%20US%20with%20the%20highest%20sympathy%20for%20the%20Palestinian%20people.%20But%20while%20the%20spread%20of%20social%20media%20and%20distrust%20of%20hitherto%20mainstream%20news%20channels%20have%20certainly%20helped%20dismantle%20the%20well%20funded%20Israeli%20narrative%20hegemony%20over%20western%20minds%2C%20to%20focus%20only%20on%20the%20medium%20and%20not%20on%20the%20content%20is%20to%20see%20only%20a%20part%20of%20the%20story.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20last%2020%20years%20have%20seen%20a%20significant%20evolution%20in%20the%20discourse%20surrounding%20the%20idea%20of%20Palestinian%20liberation%20and%20three%20themes%20specifically%20are%20making%20their%20narrative%20more%20compelling%20globally%3A%20first%2C%20shifting%20the%20liberation%20discourse%20from%20territory%20to%20equality%2C%20second%2C%20the%20description%20of%20Israel%20as%20a%20settler%20colonial%20state%20(as%20opposed%20to%20the%20Israeli%20narrative%20of%20a%20historical%20homeland)%20and%20finally%2C%20the%20rejection%20of%20the%20idea%20of%20the%20United%20States%20as%20%E2%80%9Cneutral%E2%80%9D%20party%20to%20this%20conflict.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EIn%20the%20first%20of%20a%20two%20part%20series%20on%20the%20changing%20Israel%20Palestine%20narratives%2C%20I%20examine%20the%20shift%20from%20territory%20to%20rights%20and%20what%20that%20means.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EFrom%20the%20river%20to%20the%20sea%E2%80%A6%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20precondition%20to%20a%20seat%20at%20the%20negotiating%20table%20at%20Oslo%20in%201993%2C%20the%20Yasser%20Arafat%20led%20PLO%20formally%20recognised%20the%20partition%20of%20historical%20Palestine%20and%20the%20state%20of%20Israel.%20Despite%20the%20subsequent%20failure%20of%20the%20Oslo%20accords%20to%20deliver%20on%20these%20two%20states%2C%20this%20cemented%20the%20idea%20of%20a%20%E2%80%9Ctwo%20state%20solution%E2%80%9D%20to%20the%20Palestine%20question%20in%20global%20polity.%20In%20the%2030%20years%20since%20the%20Oslo%20accords%2C%20East%20Jerusalem%20and%20the%20West%20Bank%20remain%20fully%20occupied%2C%20and%20while%20Israeli%20settlements%20were%20withdrawn%20from%20the%20Gaza%20Strip%20in%202005%2C%20the%20whole%20strip%20was%20placed%20under%20a%20harsh%20ongoing%20Israeli%20blockade%20in%202007%2C%20and%20is%20currently%20almost%20certainly%20about%20to%20be%20physically%20reoccupied%20by%20Israel.%20The%20Palestinian%20Authority%2C%20established%20pursuant%20to%20the%20Oslo%20accords%20has%20proven%20to%20be%20ineffective%20in%20protecting%20the%20rights%20of%20Palestinians%20living%20in%20the%20occupied%20territories%20or%20halting%20the%20illegal%20construction%20of%20settlements%20in%20these%20territories%20and%20the%20US%20contribution%20to%20the%20creation%20of%20the%20two%20states%20has%20rarely%20extended%20beyond%20the%20very%20occasional%20reprimand%20to%20Israel%20on%20their%20settlement%20policy%20(also%20by%20and%20large%20given%20up%20in%20recent%20times).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnd%20yet%20the%20framing%20of%20this%20conflict%20as%20some%20sort%20of%20a%20territorial%20dispute%20between%20two%20states%20has%20allowed%20Israeli%20and%20American%20voices%20to%20shift%20attention%20away%20from%20the%20systemic%20injustices%20deployed%20against%20Palestinians%20living%20under%20Israeli%20military%20rule%20in%20a%20seemingly%20never-ending%20occupation.%20As%20per%20the%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ohchr.org%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2Fdocuments%2Fcountries%2Fpalestine%2Fa-78-545-auv.pdf%5C%22%3EUN%20special%20rapporteur%20on%20the%20occupied%20territories%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20these%20deprivations%20include%20detention%20and%20trial%20by%20military%20tribunal%20for%20children%20as%20young%20as%2012%2C%20administrative%20imprisonment%20without%20trial%2C%20apartheid%20style%20restrictions%20on%20movement%20within%20the%20territory%2C%20the%20arbitrary%20bulldozing%20of%20Palestinian%20homes%20and%20the%20illegal%20appropriation%20of%20Palestinian%20homes%20and%20lands%20by%20Israeli%20settlers.%20Gaza%2C%20prior%20to%20the%20current%20offensive%2C%20had%20been%20turned%20by%20the%20Israeli%20blockade%20into%20what%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.hrw.org%2Fnews%2F2022%2F06%2F14%2Fgaza-israels-open-air-prison-15%5C%22%3EHuman%20Rights%20Watch%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0termed%20an%20%E2%80%9Copen%20air%20prison%E2%80%9D.%20Even%20within%20Israel%2C%20Palestinians%2C%20despite%20making%20up%2020%25%20of%20the%20population%20and%20holding%20Israeli%20citizenship%20are%20deprived%20of%20certain%20important%20rights%20reserved%20for%20Jewish%20citizens%2C%20including%20their%20right%20to%20freely%20reside%20in%20and%20around%20hundreds%20of%20earmarked%20Jewish%20majority%20communities%2C%20and%20since%202018%2C%20the%20right%20of%20self%20determination.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPalestinian%20scholars%2C%20responding%20to%20this%20reality%2C%20have%20shifted%20the%20paradigms%20of%20the%20discourse.%20Instead%20of%20focusing%20on%20the%20theoretical%20possibility%20of%20a%20future%20with%20an%20independent%20territory%20and%20what%20those%20territorial%20boundaries%20might%20look%20like%2C%20they%20have%20chosen%20to%20focus%20on%20the%20reality%20that%20exists%20today%20between%20the%20river%20Jordan%20and%20the%20Mediterranean%20Sea%2C%20namely%20Palestinians%20and%20Jews%20living%20under%20the%20control%20of%20a%20single%20state%20%E2%80%94%20Israel%20%E2%80%94%20but%20with%20vastly%20unequal%20rights.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20solution%20to%20this%2C%20first%20suggested%20somewhat%20hesitantly%20by%20British%20Palestinian%20scholar%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fwww.miftah.org%2FDisplay.cfm%3FDocId%3D1690%26CategoryId%3D8%5C%22%3EGhada%20Karmi%20in%202003%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20since%20with%20greater%20force%20by%20others%2C%20is%20the%20creation%20of%20a%20single%20democratic%20secular%20state%20with%20a%20one-man%2C%20one-vote%20polity%20without%20reference%20to%20ethnicity%20or%20creed.%20Prominent%20Palestinian%20American%20scholar%2C%20Rashid%20Khalidi%20articulates%20this%20less%20directly%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThere%20are%20now%20two%20peoples%20in%20Palestine%2C%20irrespective%20of%20how%20they%20came%20into%20being%2C%20the%20conflict%20between%20them%20cannot%20be%20resolved%20as%20long%20as%20the%20national%20existence%20of%20each%20is%20denied%20by%20the%20other.%20Their%20mutual%20acceptance%20can%20only%20be%20based%20on%20complete%20equality%20of%20rights%2C%20including%20national%20rights%2C%20notwithstanding%20the%20historical%20differences%20between%20the%20two.%20There%20is%20no%20other%20possible%20sustainable%20solution%2C%20barring%20the%20unthinkable%20notion%20of%20one%20people%E2%80%99s%20extermination%20by%20the%20other.%20Overcoming%20the%20resistance%20of%20those%20who%20benefit%20from%20the%20status%20quo%2C%20in%20order%20to%20ensure%20equal%20rights%20for%20all%20in%20this%20small%20country%20between%20the%20Jordan%20River%20and%20the%20sea%20%E2%80%93%20this%20is%20a%20test%20of%20the%20political%20ingenuity%20of%20all%20concerned.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EInterestingly%2C%20despite%20the%20extreme%20violence%20of%20October%207%2C%20and%20their%20own%20socially%20conservative%20Islamist%20origins%2C%20senior%20members%20of%20Hamas%20seem%20to%20be%20trying%20to%20publicly%20at%20least%20align%20with%20this%20idea%20of%20a%20pluralistic%20Palestine%20based%20on%20equality.%20The%20demands%20made%20this%20time%20(the%20return%20of%20Palestinians%20detained%20in%20Israeli%20prisons)%20seem%20designed%20to%20publicise%20the%20human%20rights%20violations%20faced%20by%20Palestinians%20in%20Israeli%20prisons.%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3DAGL3mkKQ8ng%5C%22%3ESpeaking%20to%20veteran%20Indian%20journalist%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Karan%20Thapar%2C%20Dr.%20Musa%20Abu%20Marzou%2C%20the%20head%20of%20Hamas%E2%80%99%20international%20relations%20body%2C%20offered%20his%20personal%20view%20of%20a%20solution%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CActually%20the%20main%20solution%20would%20be%20the%20one%20state%20solution%20as%20historical%20Palestine%20would%20be%20liberated%20for%20Palestinian%20Arabs%20of%20all%20religions%20%E2%80%93%20Muslims%2C%20Christians%2C%20Jews%2C%20a%20country%20that%20will%20contain%20all%20of%20those%20categories%2C%20without%20discrimination%2C%20open%20religion%20or%20open%20anything%20else.%20This%20Palestine%20will%20give%20citizenship%20only%20in%20the%20criteria%20of%20residence%2C%20not%20discrimination%20or%20apartheid.%20This%20is%20the%20only%20solution%20I%20am%20seeing%20right%20now%E2%80%A6This%20is%20my%20personal%20opinion.%20I%20believe%20that%20a%20one%20state%20solution%20as%20Palestine%20with%20same%20rights%20for%20all%20of%20its%20citizens-%20Muslims%2C%20Jews%20and%20Christians.%20Same%20rights%20and%20same%20duties.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20their%20credibility%20of%20this%20statement%20with%20respect%20to%20the%20rights%20of%20Jews%20within%20historical%20Palestine%20will%20naturally%20be%20subject%20to%20a%20high%20degree%20of%20skepticism%20in%20the%20aftermath%20of%20October%207%2C%20the%20statement%20remains%20interesting.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20Rashid%20Khalidi%20points%20out%2C%20with%20a%20total%20Arab%20population%20in%20Palestine%20and%20Israel%20that%20is%20roughly%20equal%20to%20or%20slightly%20higher%20than%20the%20Jewish%20population%2C%20the%20maintenance%20of%20the%20Zionist%20project%20necessarily%20requires%20either%20the%20continuation%20of%20the%20current%20systemic%20inequalities%20or%20the%20utterly%20unthinkable%20idea%20of%20another%20mass%20expulsion%20of%20the%20Palestinians%20along%20the%20lines%20of%201948%20and%201967.%20By%20shifting%20the%20focus%20from%20territory%20to%20equality%2C%20Palestinian%20scholars%20have%20made%20either%20of%20these%20ideas%20increasingly%20difficult%20for%20young%20progressives%20in%20the%20west%20to%20stomach.%20Palestinian%20content%20creators%20have%20built%20off%20this.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEven%20prior%20to%20October%207%2C%20some%20of%20the%20most%20popular%20Palestinian%20content%20on%20social%20media%20was%20focused%20on%20visually%20documenting%20the%20inequalities%20faced%20by%20Palestinians%20in%20their%20everyday%20lives%20in%20the%20occupied%20territories%20in%20Jerusalem%20or%20the%20West%20Bank%20and%20the%20Gaza%20Strip.%20I%20wrote%20in%202021%20of%20the%20young%20Palestinians%20in%20the%20East%20Jerusalem%20neighbourhood%20of%20Sheik%20Jarrah%20effectively%20using%20social%20media%20to%20highlight%20their%20own%20struggle%20against%20evictions%20from%20their%20homes.%20Viral%20videos%2C%20including%20one%20of%20a%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.aljazeera.com%2Fnews%2F2021%2F5%2F4%2Fif-i-dont-steal-your-home-someone-else-will-jewish-settler-says%5C%22%3Esettler%20from%20New%20York%20telling%20a%20Palestinian%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0woman%20in%20East%20Jerusalem%20that%20if%20he%20didn%E2%80%99t%20steal%20her%20home%2C%20someone%20else%20would%20have%2C%20have%20driven%20home%20these%20inequalities%20in%20young%20western%20minds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESince%20October%207%2C%20these%20ideas%20have%20only%20been%20cemented.%20While%20there%20is%20naturally%20a%20great%20deal%20of%20sympathy%20for%20the%20Israeli%20civilian%20victims%20and%20hostages%20of%20October%207%2C%20the%20idea%20that%20the%202.2%20million%20strong%20predominantly%20civilian%20population%20of%20Gaza%20can%20be%20trapped%20in%20a%20small%20strip%20of%20land%2C%20internally%20displaced%2C%20deprived%20of%20water%2C%20electricity%20and%20medical%20care%20and%20bombed%20incessantly%20for%20weeks%20on%20end%20at%20the%20will%20of%20Israel%20has%20highlighted%20the%20inherent%20inequality%20of%20the%20Palestinian%20condition%20like%20never%20before.%20Young%20Palestinians%20on%20ground%20in%20Gaza%20have%20provided%20an%20unfiltered%20view%20of%20the%20practical%20import%20of%20this%20inequality%20%E2%80%93%20the%20horrors%20of%20the%20bombardment%20and%20siege%20%E2%80%93%20which%20cannot%20be%20unseen%2C%20and%20are%20likely%20to%20shape%20progressive%20views%20in%20the%20West%20for%20years%20to%20come.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Zionist%20intellectual%20response%20to%20this%20challenge%20has%20veered%20between%20wholly%20inadequate%20to%20wildly%20counterproductive.%20The%20usual%20strategy%20of%20equating%20all%20criticism%20of%20the%20state%20of%20Israel%20with%20anti-semitism%20has%20had%20limited%20efficacy%20this%20time%2C%20partly%20due%20to%20the%20substantial%20number%20of%20progressive%20Jews%20in%20America%20joining%20calls%20for%20a%20ceasefire%2C%20and%20partly%20due%20to%20harsh%20actions%20like%20doxxing%20students%20on%20campuses%2C%20getting%20people%20fired%20and%20job%20offers%20revoked%2C%20which%20have%20only%20served%20to%20reinforce%20rather%20than%20counter%20the%20impression%20of%20a%20high%20handed%20colonial%20state%20in%20young%20minds.%20It%20hasn%E2%80%99t%20helped%20that%20many%20of%20the%20students%20and%20young%20people%20harassed%20in%20this%20manner%20have%20been%20Black%20or%20from%20other%20ethnic%20minorities.%20Attempts%20to%20conflate%20Hamas%20with%20the%20Nazis%20have%20only%20resulted%20(rightfully)%20in%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fcommentisfree%2F2023%2Foct%2F24%2Fisrael-gaza-palestinians-holocaust%5C%22%3Ecriticism%20from%20prominent%20genocide%20scholars%C2%A0%3C%2Fa%3Eof%20Zionists%20minimising%20the%20horrors%20of%20the%20Holocaust%20to%20serve%20current%20interests.%20The%20attempts%20to%20conflate%20all%20sympathy%20for%20the%20Palestinian%20cause%20with%20support%20for%20terror%20have%20also%20had%20limited%20success%20with%20younger%20people%20with%20the%20western%20media%E2%80%99s%20incessant%20%E2%80%9Cdo%20you%20condemn%20Hamas%E2%80%9D%20line%20of%20questioning%20turning%20into%20a%20TikTok%20punchline.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20only%20direct%20counter%20to%20this%20reframing%20of%20liberation%20as%20equality%20has%20been%20the%20attempt%20to%20equate%20the%20Palestinian%20call%20for%20a%20single%20democratic%20state%20to%20a%20call%20for%20the%20genocidal%20destruction%20of%20all%20Jews%20between%20the%20river%20Jordan%20and%20the%20Mediterranean%20Sea.%20This%20has%20had%20mixed%20success.%20US%20Congresswoman%20Rashida%20Tlaib%20was%20censured%20by%20her%20House%20colleagues%20for%20saying%20%E2%80%9Cfrom%20the%20river%20to%20the%20sea%2C%20Palestine%20will%20be%20free%E2%80%9D%2C%20and%20Elon%20Musk%2C%20the%20owner%20of%20the%20social%20media%20platform%20X%20(formerly%20Twitter)%20has%20classified%20the%20slogan%20as%20%E2%80%9Cgenocidal%20speech%E2%80%9D.%20And%20yet%20immediately%20after%20Musk%E2%80%99s%20slogan%20ban%2C%20it%20was%20trending%20on%20the%20platform.%20Similarly%2C%20a%20young%20Democrat%20chose%20to%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.newsweek.com%2Fdemocrat-confirms-offer-challenge-rashida-tlaib-1846257%23%3A~%3Atext%3DOne%2520of%2520AIPAC%2527s%2520biggest%2520donors%2Cphone%2520call%2520to%2520turn%2520public.%5C%22%3Epublicly%20refuse%C2%A0%3C%2Fa%3Ea%20US%20%24%2020%20million%20donation%20from%20AIPAC%20(the%20pro-Israel%20lobbying%20group)%20to%20run%20against%20Tlaib%20in%20the%20next%20primaries%2C%20which%20indicates%20that%20as%20far%20as%20young%20progressives%20are%20concerned%2C%20this%20argument%20has%20by%20and%20large%20not%20found%20traction.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20logical%20counter%20for%20the%20Israelis%2C%20as%20was%20the%20case%20for%20Yitzhak%20Rabin%20when%20faced%20with%20the%201987%20Intifada%2C%20would%20be%20to%20offer%20minor%20concessions%20to%20the%20two%20state%20solution%20and%20shift%20the%20debate%20away%20from%20rights%20and%20towards%20territory%20again.%20But%20this%20is%20a%20step%20that%20neither%20Netanyahu%E2%80%99s%20far%20right%20government%20nor%20Joe%20Biden%E2%80%99s%20administration%20has%20left%20itself%20with%20the%20ability%20to%20engineer%20anymore.%20From%20the%20Trump%20administration%20unilaterally%20recognising%20Jerusalem%20as%20the%20capital%20of%20Israel%20in%202018%20to%20the%20Biden%20administration%E2%80%99s%20failure%20to%20impose%20any%20restrictions%20on%20the%20Israeli%20massacres%20committed%20in%20Gaza%20in%20the%20last%2049%20days%2C%20the%20US%20has%20for%20all%20practical%20purposes%20publicly%20declared%20itself%20to%20be%20a%20partisan%20in%20the%20conflict%20making%20it%20impossible%20for%20them%20to%20go%20back%20to%20their%201990s%20role%20as%20a%20serious%20mediator%20in%20the%20Middle%20East.%20It%20is%20telling%20that%20they%20have%20not%20been%20at%20the%20fore%20of%20hostage%20negotiations%2C%20despite%20US%20citizens%20being%20involved.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fauthor%2Fsarayu-pani%5C%22%3ESarayu%20Pani%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0is%20a%20former%20lawyer%20and%20tweets%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fsarayupani%5C%22%3E%40sarayupani%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20article%20first%20appeared%20on%20the%20author%E2%80%99s%20Substack%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Ftattva.substack.com%2F%5C%22%3E%E2%80%98Tattva%E2%80%99%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20has%20been%20republished%20with%20permission.%20Read%20the%20original%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftattva.substack.com%2Fp%2Fits-more-than-tiktok%5C%22%3Ehere%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1701002604000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fupload